Protection of Work and Property. Contractor shall continuously maintain adequate
protection of all work and materials under this Contract from damage caused by Contractor's
equipment, personnel or subcontractors until final completion of the work and shall protect the
property from injury caused by Contractor's equipment, personnel or subcontractors until final
completion of the work.' Contractor shall repair any damage suffered or resulting from any such
failure to maintain-such protection as aforesaid and shall repair any damage at its own cost and
expense to the satisfaction of Owner.
10.
Cleaning Up. >Contractor shall leave property clean and ready for occupancy.
11.
Safety: Indemnity.
(a)
Contractor will be responsible for initiating, maintaining and supervising all
safety precautions and programs in connection with the work. Contractor will take all necessary
precautions for the safety of, and will provide the necessary protection to prevent damage, injury
or loss to:
(1)
all employees of Contractor, its subcontractors and employees; and
(ii)
all the work and all materials or equipment to be incorporated therein, whether in
storage on or off the job site; and
(iii)
other property of Contractor at the job site or otherwise situated in or on the
property.
(b)
Contractor will comply with all applicable laws, ordinances, rules, regulations and
orders of any public or quasi-public body having jurisdiction for the safety of persons or property
or for their protection from damage, injury or loss.
12.
Insurance. During the term of this Contract and until final completion of the work
and delivery of possession to Owner, Contractor shall carry and maintain all builder's risk
insurance in an amount not less than the Contract Sum, covering all improvements and building
materials, with mortgagee loss payable in favor of Bank, naming both Contractor and Owner as
insured thereunder.
13.
Completion by Contractor. But Not Bank: Contractor shall be obligated to
complete all work in accordance with this Contract and Bank shall not be responsible for the
completion of the improvements and shall not in any manner be considered a guarantor of
performance by Contractor. Contractor agrees to indemnify and hold Bank, its successors and
assigns, harmless against all claims for completion of the improvethents.
